  "abstract": "LLMs, particularly GPT-4o subscription-based, show potential as tools for training informal caregivers by providing tailored guidance and reducing errors. Although not yet surpassing professional instruction quality, these models offer a flexible and accessible alternative that could enhance home safety and care quality. Further research is necessary to address limitations and optimize their performance. Future implementation of LLMs may alleviate health care system burdens by reducing common caregiver errors.",
